FG-506 — Mootness-Based Lift (Risk Gone, Record Shows It)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: If the risk is moot (deadline passed, task done), ask to lift with pins.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Show what mooted the harm (date-stamped exhibit); explain why no residual risk; propose vacatur or lift.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 6-line mootness lift with one dated exhibit pin.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Print window closed 09/05 (Vendor Decl ¶7; Ex A:1). No residual risk; lift stay or vacate ¶3.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: When the harm dies, the stay should too.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A calendar page crossed out with “window closed.”

⸻

FG-507 — Intervening Law Modification (Clarify or Lift)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: New authority can narrow or end a stay—quote it, don’t argue it.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Cite the holding line from the new case; pin your record; propose a clarify line or lift; attach tick-box order.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 7-line motion citing one intervening case and one record pin.
	•	✅ Model Response: “New case confirms factor findings required; here, harm not reached (Dkt 18:2). Clarify scope to ¶3 parties only or lift.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: A rule sentence + pin > re-briefing.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A new case tile pointing to a smaller stay bracket.

⸻

FG-508 — Compliance-Based Narrowing (Reward What’s Done)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: If key tasks are completed, narrow the stay to the rest.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: List completed steps with pins; propose removing those steps from scope; keep short sunset for any remainder.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 6-line compliance narrowing with two proof pins.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Tasks A/B complete (Dkt 101:2–3; Ex B:1). Narrow stay to ¶3 only; sunset 21 days; status 14d.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Reward progress with precision.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A checklist with two green checks and one remaining box.

⸻

FG-509 — Third-Party Carve-Out (Vendors • Agencies • Innocents)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Protect non-parties with an explicit carve-out.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: One sentence: no obligations on non-party vendors/agencies/innocents; limit scope to parties; report instead of restrain.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a carve-out sentence for your live stay.
	•	✅ Model Response: “No obligations are imposed on non-party vendors; scope remains as to parties only; weekly reporting.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Carve-outs survive appeal.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A bracketed paragraph with a small “vendors carved out” tag.
